In src/services/api.js : We can change the AI requirements and give the appropriate prompts.

Charts or summary is required.

Add pdf download feature. Prompt is 
"Build a "Claim Certificate" section on the ProjectDetail page, where a company volunteer can:

Enter their name

Enter a 5-character special code (pre-assigned)

If the code matches a valid entry in the system (from DB):

✅ Show a "Download Certificate" button

🧾 Generate a PDF certificate dynamically with their name and project name

💾 Allow them to download it"

"🧩 Frontend Tasks
Component: ClaimCertificateSection.jsx
Form Fields:

Input: Volunteer Name

Input: Special Code (placeholder: "e.g., A1B2C")

Validation:

Ensure name is not empty

Ensure code is 5 characters long

Submit Button → POST to backend /api/certify/validate-code

If success response:

Display PDF certificate preview (optional)

Show Download Certificate button

Use jspdf or react-pdf to generate the PDF with:

Volunteer Name

Project Name

NGO/Company name

Date of completion", etc in ChatGPT. 